cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network design problem.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for finding a minimum cost subgraph.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and connectivity requirements.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with optimization of a network design problem.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with finding a subgraph satisfying connectivity requirements.
